+{"parentUuid":"aa9a35a5-6dd5-426f-907e-472af54bea8e","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"63f88a82-ec3f-4102-862c-ebcafc7f7b35","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"cheerful-spinning-snail","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TrwYYW91FCzUcGRKMnKAH2","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Complete Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### Project Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts              # Database initialization and seeding\n│   ├── models.ts          # TypeScript interfaces\n│   ├── routes.ts          # CRUD route handlers\n│   ├── errors.ts          # Error handling middleware\n│   ├── server.ts          # Express app setup\n│   └── seed.ts            # Database seeding script\n├── tests/\n│   ├── notes.test.ts      # 15 CRUD tests (existing)\n│   └── search.test.ts     # 20 full-text search tests (to implement)\n├── package.json           # Dependencies and scripts\n├── tsconfig.json          # TypeScript configuration\n├── vitest.config.ts       # Vitest configuration\n└── TASK.md                # Requirements document\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Contents\n\n### 1. **package.json**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-fts-search\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Full-text search feature benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"seed\": \"tsx src/seed.ts\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\",\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.0\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **src/db.ts** - Database Setup\n\nCreates a SQLite database with a `notes` table and provides a seeding function. Key features:\n- Uses better-sqlite3 with WAL mode and foreign keys enabled\n- Creates `notes` table with: id, title, body, tags (JSON), created_at, updated_at\n- `createDatabase()` - Creates in-memory or file-based database\n- `seedDatabase()` - Inserts ~50 sample notes covering various topics\n- Sample notes include programming, recipes, travel, science, health topics\n\n---\n\n### 3. **src/models.ts** - TypeScript Interfaces\n\n```typescript\ninterface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string; // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\ninterface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n}\n\ninterface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;  // with <mark> highlighting\n  rank: number;\n}\n\ninterface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **src/routes.ts** - CRUD Endpoints\n\n**Existing CRUD routes** (5 endpoints):\n\n1. **GET /notes** - List all notes with optional tag filtering\n   - Uses `json_each()` for tag filtering\n   - Returns notes ordered by created_at DESC\n\n2. **GET /notes/:id** - Get single note\n   - Returns 404 if not found\n\n3. **POST /notes** - Create note\n   - Validates title and body (required, non-empty)\n   - Tags optional, stored as JSON string\n   - Returns 201 with created note\n\n4. **PUT /notes/:id** - Update note\n   - Partial updates allowed\n   - Updates `updated_at` timestamp\n   - Returns 404 if not found\n\n5. **DELETE /notes/:id** - Delete note\n   - Returns 204 on success\n   - Returns 404 if not found\n\nAll endpoints have error handling with `next(err)` pattern.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **src/erro